title: A PHASE 2 MULTICENTER, DOUBLE BLIND, PLACEBO CONTROLLED, PARALLEL GROUP STUDY OF PF-04447943 IN SUBJECTS WITH MILD TO MODERATE ALZHEIMER'S DISEASE
description_brief: The purpose of this study is to evaluate the effects of PF-04447943 compared to placebo on cognitive, behavioral and overall symptoms of Alzheimer's disease; evaluate the safety and tolerability of PF-0444793 compared to placebo; and determine the levels of PF-04447943 in the plasma over the course of the study.

outcomeMeasures.title: Alzheimer's Disease Assessment Scale-Cognitive Subscale 70 (ADAS-Cog 70) Score at Baseline
outcomeMeasures.description: ADAS-cog is a structured scale assessing the severity of cognitive impairment in Alzheimer's disease. It comprises of following 11 items (range): word recall (0-10), naming objects and fingers (0-5), following commands (0-5), constructional praxis (0-5), ideational praxis (0-5), orientation (0-8), word recognition (0-12), recall of test instructions (0-5), spoken language ability (0-5), word-finding difficulty (0-5), comprehension of spoken language (0-5). Total ADAS-cog 70 score was sum of all items and ranged from 0 (least impairment) to 70 (most severe impairment), higher score indicating worse cognition.

outcomeMeasures.title: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Total Score at Baseline

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Participants With Laboratory Test Abnormalities
outcomeMeasures.description: Criteria for laboratory test abnormality: a) Hematology: white blood cells (WBC) \<0.6\*lower limit of normal (LLN)/\>1.5\*upper limit of normal (ULN), hemoglobin, hematocrit, red blood cells (RBC), lymphocytes \<0.8\*LLN, total neutrophils \<0.8\*LLN/ \>1.2\*ULN, basophils, eosinophils, monocytes \>1.2\*ULN; b) Liver Function: total bilirubin \>1.5\*ULN, aspartate aminotransferase (AT), alanine AT\[\>0.3\*ULN, total protein, albumin \<0.8\*LLN/ \>1.2\*ULN; c) Renal Function: creatinine \>1.3\*ULN, uric acid \>1.2\*ULN; d) Electrolytes: sodium \<0.95\*LLN/ \>1.05\*ULN, potassium, chloride, bicarbonate \<0.9\*LLN/ \>1.1\*ULN; e) Clinical Chemistry: glucose \<0.6\*LLN/ \>1.5\*ULN, glycosylated hemoglobin \>1.3\*ULN; f) Urinalysis: ketones, protein, blood/hemoglobin, urine glucose \>=1, RBC, WBC \>=6, hyaline casts \>1; g) Hormones: tetraiodothyronine (T4), triiodothyronine (T3) and thyroid stimulating hormone (TSH) \<0.8\*LLN/1.2\*ULN.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Participants With Pre-defined Criteria for Electrocardiogram (ECG) Abnormalities

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Participants With Pre-defined Criteria of Vital Signs Abnormalities
outcomeMeasures.description: Pre-defined criteria vital signs abnormalities included maximum increase or decrease of greater than or equal to (\>=) 30 millimeters of mercury (mmHg) from baseline for supine systolic blood pressure (SBP); maximum increase or decrease of \>=20 mmHg from baseline for supine diastolic BP (DBP); maximum increase or decrease of \>=30 mmHg from baseline for standing SBP; maximum increase or decrease of \>=20 mmHg from baseline for standing DBP. Orthostatic hypotension was defined as a drop of more than 10 mmHg in diastolic BP or a drop of more than 20 mmHg in systolic BP within 3 minutes of standing from the supine position.

explanation_target: Reason: PF-04447943 is a small‑molecule selective PDE9A inhibitor that elevates cGMP to enhance synaptic plasticity and memory — the trial's stated aim was to evaluate effects on cognition, behavior and overall symptoms rather than targeting amyloid or tau directly. citeturn0search2turn0search5.

Act: Key trial details — Phase 2, randomized, double‑blind, placebo‑controlled, 12 weeks, primary outcome ADAS‑cog (cognitive endpoint). The drug is described in clinical reports as a PDE9A inhibitor (small molecule). These characteristics point to a symptomatic cognitive enhancement strategy rather than a biologic or an anti‑amyloid/tau disease‑modifying approach. citeturn0search0turn0search1.

Reflect: Although some preclinical work reported preservation of dendritic spine density in APP transgenic mice (suggesting potential neuroprotective effects), the mechanism (PDE9 inhibition to boost cGMP and synaptic function) and the trial endpoints (cognition/behavior) align best with the 'cognitive enhancer' category rather than a disease‑targeted biologic or small‑molecule anti‑amyloid/tau agent. Note: the published Phase 2 report found no significant cognitive or behavioral benefit at 12 weeks. citeturn0search2turn0search0.
Web search results used: PubMed summary and Phase 2 trial report describing PF‑04447943 as a selective PDE9A inhibitor and the Phase 2 outcomes. citeturn0search0turn0search2turn0search5.
explanation_agent: Reason: The investigational drug PF-04447943 is a selective phosphodiesterase‑9A (PDE9A) inhibitor that raises cGMP and is intended to enhance synaptic plasticity and memory (a symptomatic/cognitive‑enhancer approach) rather than directly targeting amyloid or tau pathology. citeturn0search3turn0search2.

Act: Key extracted details — PF-04447943 is a brain‑penetrant, selective PDE9A small‑molecule inhibitor (mechanism: elevates cGMP to boost synaptic function). The cited Phase 2 trial was a 12‑week, randomized, double‑blind, placebo‑controlled study in mild‑to‑moderate AD with ADAS‑cog as the primary outcome and found no significant cognitive or behavioral benefit. These characteristics map to CADRO category M (Synaptic Plasticity/Neuroprotection) because the intended mechanism is to enhance synaptic plasticity and cognition rather than to modify amyloid, tau, inflammation, or other disease pathways. citeturn0search0turn0search3.

Reflect: The classification as M is consistent with preclinical data showing improved LTP, increased synapse markers, and prevention of dendritic spine loss in APP transgenic mice, and with the trial’s cognitive/symptomatic focus and endpoints. The intervention is not primarily anti‑amyloid, anti‑tau, inflammatory, vascular, or diagnostic, nor does the description indicate multiple distinct mechanistic targets, so 'M) Synaptic Plasticity/Neuroprotection' is the most specific CADRO match. citeturn0search3turn0search0.
